-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-06-09/yankees-joba-chamberlain-likely-needs-season-ending-surgery-ny-post-says.html
Joba Chamberlain of the  New York
Yankees  probably needs season-ending surgery on a torn ligament
in his pitching arm, the New York Post said, quoting manager  Joe
Girardi .  Chamberlain was placed on the disabled list yesterday with
a sore elbow. Girardi said today that the right-handed relief
pitcher probably would require ligament replacement surgery,
known as Tommy John surgery, and be out for 12 months.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Larry Siddons at 
 lsiddons@bloomberg.net  